WEBVTT



00:00:00.896 --> 00:00:08.768
Well hello friends and thank you for joining me in our daily reading from God's Holy Word. Today we're reading Mark chapter 10.

00:00:08.544 --> 00:00:10.528
Verses 1 to 12.

00:00:10.848 --> 00:00:12.352
In this lesson,

00:00:12.320 --> 00:00:15.936
Jesus teaches us about the blessing of marriage

00:00:15.712 --> 00:00:17.920
And the sorrow of divorce.

00:00:18.016 --> 00:00:19.936
In speaking of it,

00:00:19.936 --> 00:00:25.216
He points us to his love, his patience and his faithfulness.

00:00:25.248 --> 00:00:26.848
Now before we read

00:00:26.624 --> 00:00:27.872
Let's pray.

00:00:28.544 --> 00:00:33.984
Our Father in heaven, teach us your word and then help us to walk in your ways.

00:00:34.144 --> 00:00:36.224
In Jesus' name I pray.

00:00:36.448 --> 00:00:37.664
Amen.

00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:42.176
Amen. Mark chapter 10, verses 1 to 12.

00:00:42.368 --> 00:00:51.552
And he left there and went to the region of Judea and beyond the Jordan, and crowds gathered to him again and again, as was his custom.

00:00:51.328 --> 00:00:52.800
He taught them.

00:00:52.928 --> 00:00:57.248
And Pharisees came up, and in order to test him, asked,

00:00:57.568 --> 00:01:01.216
Is it lawful for a man to divorce his wife?

00:01:01.344 --> 00:01:02.784
And he answered them,

00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:04.992
What did Moses command you?

00:01:05.184 --> 00:01:12.032
They said Moses allowed a man to write a certificate of divorce and to send her away.

00:01:12.160 --> 00:01:17.792
Jesus said to them, "Because of your hardness of heart, he wrote you this commandment."

00:01:17.792 --> 00:01:20.128
But from the beginning of creation,

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:23.168
God made them male and female.

00:01:22.976 --> 00:01:32.160
Therefore a man shall leave his father and mother, and hold fast to his wife, and the two shall become one flesh.

00:01:32.224 --> 00:01:34.400
So they are no longer two.

00:01:34.176 --> 00:01:35.808
But one flash.

00:01:35.808 --> 00:01:39.168
and what therefore God has joined together.

00:01:39.168 --> 00:01:41.664
Let not man separate.

00:01:42.592 --> 00:01:43.968
And in the house

00:01:43.904 --> 00:01:47.616
The disciples asked him again about this matter.

00:01:47.488 --> 00:01:49.152
And he said to them,

00:01:49.248 --> 00:01:53.024
Whoever divorces his wife and marries another,

00:01:52.768 --> 00:01:55.136
Commits adultery against her.

00:01:55.264 --> 00:01:57.856
And if she divorces her husband,

00:01:57.472 --> 00:01:59.328
and marries another.

00:01:59.200 --> 00:02:01.344
She commits adultery.

00:02:02.656 --> 00:02:04.864
Amen. This is God's Word.

00:02:05.152 --> 00:02:15.200
Now Jesus here didn't say everything about marriage and divorce. He says more, in fact, throughout the Bible. So today we tackle a difficult subject, but brief.

00:02:14.720 --> 00:02:16.000
But briefly, let's go.

00:02:15.936 --> 00:02:19.680
And that means many helpful things will be left unsaid.

00:02:19.552 --> 00:02:22.176
But let me highlight here three things

00:02:21.920 --> 00:02:25.024
about Jesus and us first

00:02:24.864 --> 00:02:27.552
Jesus loves people

00:02:27.584 --> 00:02:30.528
So we can trust him with our relationships.

00:02:30.560 --> 00:02:38.112
The Pharisees asked him, Is it lawful for a man to divorce his wife? Now they asked him that, not because they want to help.

00:02:37.824 --> 00:02:38.848
people.

00:02:38.752 --> 00:02:48.480
and not because they care about keeping marriages together. in fact, most people in that they followed rabbi hillel when he said that a man could divorce his wife for.

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:56.416
burning the toast or over salting the food or talking so loud in the home the neighbor could hear or even speaking to a male stranger.

00:02:56.224 --> 00:03:02.272
Now, the reason the Pharisees ask Jesus about marriage is they want to trap him.

00:03:02.208 --> 00:03:08.192
to make the people distrust Jesus. Because Jesus loves people,

00:03:08.288 --> 00:03:10.368
He answers their question.

00:03:10.336 --> 00:03:17.696
he cares about people and the pain of broken relationships and he knows that the truth is good for people.

00:03:17.504 --> 00:03:19.968
Even if it hurts to hear it.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:26.656
So he speaks not to add to pain, nor to ignore pain, but because he loves people.

00:03:27.104 --> 00:03:29.024
So you can trust him.

00:03:29.056 --> 00:03:31.136
With your relationships,

00:03:31.808 --> 00:03:34.528
Now second, Jesus is patient.

00:03:34.496 --> 00:03:37.152
With relationally broken people.

00:03:37.248 --> 00:03:41.440
And we can depend on his grace in our relationships.

00:03:41.760 --> 00:03:43.968
Jesus asked them,

00:03:43.744 --> 00:03:46.048
What did Moses command you?

00:03:46.176 --> 00:03:50.368
They refer to Deuteronomy 24, where God, through Moses,

00:03:50.304 --> 00:03:53.056
Permits and regulates divorce.

00:03:52.960 --> 00:03:57.728
Jesus schools them then on their own book.

00:03:57.536 --> 00:04:01.536
He takes them to what God originally meant for marriage,

00:04:01.344 --> 00:04:08.192
Back at creation in Genesis one and two, where it says the two shall become one flesh.

00:04:08.192 --> 00:04:10.560
No longer two, but one.

00:04:10.336 --> 00:04:13.696
God joins husband and wife together.

00:04:13.568 --> 00:04:19.360
Now, the Pharisees quoted Moses in Deuteronomy as if God had gave his stamp of approval.

00:04:19.136 --> 00:04:27.104
I'm divorced. But God there wasn't commanding divorce. He was permitting and regulating it.

00:04:26.816 --> 00:04:29.120
To soften the blow of it.

00:04:28.928 --> 00:04:31.232
To ease the harm,

00:04:30.976 --> 00:04:33.376
Because of their hard hearts.

00:04:33.408 --> 00:04:41.376
I mean, a hard-hearted man who won't live with his wife, love his wife, sleep with his wife, or forgive his wife.

00:04:41.536 --> 00:04:51.584
might come to want a new wife. He may even be violent if he can't get what his hard heart wants. What should be done in that situation? Well, protect

00:04:51.104 --> 00:05:01.152
Check the wife is what God said through Moses. First, physical protection. Let the man leave, said Moses. Second, financial protection. Make him free.

00:05:00.672 --> 00:05:05.504
And make him give her a written certificate so she can prove that.

00:05:05.280 --> 00:05:12.480
To others, she is no longer married, so that she can then remarry if she wants, and not be left destitute.

00:05:12.896 --> 00:05:20.224
Third, emotional and sexual protection. keep her from being traded around like a piece of property,

00:05:20.512 --> 00:05:26.112
By not letting the husband divorce her and then remarry her and then maybe do that again and again.

00:05:26.048 --> 00:05:31.648
god was saying i want you to think real hard about this because you can't have her back.

00:05:33.184 --> 00:05:42.752
Now the rabbis mistook God's gracious provision in allowing divorce for the wife's protection because of the hard-heartedness of man.

00:05:43.072 --> 00:05:47.104
And they mistook that as God's approval of it.

00:05:47.328 --> 00:05:51.008
Yet God was permitting what he did not intend.

00:05:51.200 --> 00:05:58.784
For the sake of limiting and restraining worse things because of human hard hearts, the alternative.

00:05:58.624 --> 00:06:01.280
to God permitting and restraining

00:06:01.056 --> 00:06:03.040
Our human evil,

00:06:03.200 --> 00:06:07.008
Is God immediately and judging us for it?

00:06:07.168 --> 00:06:10.208
But then there would be no more marriages.

00:06:10.016 --> 00:06:12.032
And there would be no more world.

00:06:12.160 --> 00:06:14.112
So do you see how patient

00:06:14.112 --> 00:06:16.608
Jesus is with people.

00:06:18.336 --> 00:06:19.520
Third,

00:06:19.392 --> 00:06:23.296
Consider his faithfulness in his marriage,

00:06:23.264 --> 00:06:26.240
And look to him for help to be faithful in yours.

00:06:26.336 --> 00:06:36.384
behind the willingness of jesus to teach on a controversial topic is as we said his love for people and his patience with sinners but also this his

00:06:35.904 --> 00:06:38.400
His commitment to the gospel

00:06:38.528 --> 00:06:48.576
For marriage is meant to tell the story of the gospel. It is meant to be a human reenactment of the greatest love story ever told of God, Mary, and Mary.

00:06:48.096 --> 00:06:58.144
airing to himself, his bride, the church. Husbands then, we learn elsewhere, are to love their wives as Christ loved the church and gave himself for her.

00:06:57.664 --> 00:07:07.712
For her, wives are to respect their husbands, for the husband is the head of his wife, even as Christ is the head of the church. Now Jesus never leaves

00:07:07.232 --> 00:07:17.280
leaves his bride, never exchanges her for a different lover, and never abuses her, always loves her. This is why the two are to become one as long as they both shall.

00:07:16.800 --> 00:07:18.176
O shall live. O shall live.

00:07:17.920 --> 00:07:20.064
That's how he treats his bride.

00:07:20.288 --> 00:07:23.488
Hence, his very strong statement that in Mark,

00:07:23.328 --> 00:07:27.840
Whoever divorces his wife and marries another commits adultery against her.

00:07:27.840 --> 00:07:32.928
And if she divorces her husband and marries another, she commits adultery.

00:07:32.896 --> 00:07:38.816
He's pressing against this hard-hearted attitude that casts people off

00:07:39.040 --> 00:07:41.856
Because he doesn't cast away his bride.

00:07:42.304 --> 00:07:47.488
Now, in this statement, Mark doesn't report the exception to the rule.

00:07:47.520 --> 00:07:54.944
which Matthew does report in Matthew 19, there Jesus says, "Except for sexual immorality."

00:07:54.976 --> 00:08:05.024
If your spouse commits adultery, you are free to divorce and to remarry. You don't have to, but you can. And then also in 1 Corinthians 10:11,

00:08:04.544 --> 00:08:07.584
1 Corinthians 7, Jesus through the apostle, 1 Corinthians

00:08:07.296 --> 00:08:12.512
adds desertion. If an unbelieving spouse deserts you,

00:08:12.256 --> 00:08:14.208
You are free to remarry.

00:08:14.240 --> 00:08:22.080
the point is Jesus is faithful he wants us to be faithful and he can help us be faithful

00:08:21.792 --> 00:08:26.784
1. Don't fear then to ask him to make you faithful. 2.

00:08:27.008 --> 00:08:32.672
Because he loves us and is patient with us, having died for our unfaithfulness.

00:08:32.416 --> 00:08:34.304
married us.

00:08:34.048 --> 00:08:35.680
As his beloved.

00:08:36.064 --> 00:08:37.984
J. C. Ryle says,

00:08:37.856 --> 00:08:47.904
Happy are they who, in the matter of marriage, observe three rules. The first is to marry only in the Lord, and after prayer for God's approval and blood.

00:08:47.424 --> 00:08:48.544
and blessing.

00:08:48.416 --> 00:08:51.968
The second is not to expect too much.

00:08:51.840 --> 00:08:53.280
From their partners.

00:08:53.152 --> 00:08:57.408
And to remember that marriage is, after all, the union of two sinners.

00:08:57.280 --> 00:08:59.168
And not of two angels.

00:08:59.392 --> 00:09:04.768
The third rule is to strive first and foremost for one another's sanctification.

00:09:04.672 --> 00:09:06.496
The more holy

00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:08.320
married people are.

00:09:08.352 --> 00:09:10.240
The happier they are.

00:09:11.232 --> 00:09:12.480
Let's pray.

00:09:12.960 --> 00:09:15.296
Father in heaven, make it so.

00:09:15.328 --> 00:09:17.440
And forgive our failures.

00:09:17.280 --> 00:09:21.216
And help us to love as we have been loved by you.

00:09:21.536 --> 00:09:23.232
Jesus name

00:09:23.232 --> 00:09:24.416
Amen.

00:09:24.512 --> 00:09:26.560
Well, thank you for listening in.

00:09:26.336 --> 00:09:28.256
I hope you'll join me next time
